metadata.name: Dubious Floofs #53
metadata.description:
These little guys love to run around in grassy hills and meadows, but they can get easily distracted...

I designed this so that it will always fit to the height of your window. That means you can adjust the window width and refresh to uncover more of the terrain. Enjoy!

metadata.name: contrapuntos #741
metadata.description:
Musical counterpoint is to me an abstraction of the layered, intertwining rhythms of every activity we carry on in our lives. With a global tempo typically set in days, we fit all sorts of temporal structures where our joys and fears live and play out over the span of our lives. This series is a metaphorical transposition of the musical counterpoint into a visual space, sometimes with repeating patterns, sometimes with broken structures, sometimes isolated notes / hours / souls.

Artwork by Marcelo Soria-Rodríguez, @msoriaro. Made with p5js & glsl.

metadata.name: DeStijl Fortunes #252
metadata.description:
The best part of being full and happy and ready to leave the restaurant is opening the fortune cookie. Does it mean something? Does it have poor grammar and vague references? You know it's not really *for you* but it sure feels like it.
This collab between sgt_slaughtermelon and 0xphiiil creates simple pleasant DeStijl-influenced designs determined by your hash and inspired by Theo Van Doesburg that feature crypto-centric fortunes. Maybe they'll give you some *not financial advice* or maybe it will be a vague truism or an optimistic or pessimistic omen. Who knows? Part of the fun is imagining that it's for you and it's real - and if you don't like it, just open another cookie.

metadata.name: Coupé Décalé #3
metadata.description:
Coupé-Décalé is a type of popular dance music originating in Côte d'Ivoire (Ivory Coast).
The term Coupé-Décalé means cut-shifted in french.
A name that perfectly defines the process used in this generative series.

Artist: Estienne
Dec. 2021 / Jan. 2022

metadata.name: Bougainvillea #94
SoulSea #169
metadata.description:
The Soul Sea

You look down and find that the ocean in your heart is a sine wave. 
The tide gently laps onto the shore.

The soul is the sea. You are the land. 
There are waves on the shore, and the waves are slices.

Gazing at the slices, you feel the coldness of the Arctic Ocean, the permafrost of the Antarctic Sea, the deep darkness of the bottomless sea.

Stay silent, hear the sound of the waves lapping at the innumerable shores far away.
Feel the soul of the digital ocean.

Interactivities:
> Key P: Pause
> Key S: Save
> Press and move mouseX: wave moves slower / faster

Che-Yu Wu
